On March 29th, the Chamber held the opening event of our "BRIC Effect"&amp;nbsp; seminar series. Drawing on our broad in-house international expertise and featuring discussions with renowned thinkers and authorities, this three-part series explores the evolving political and economic influence of Brazil, Russia, India and China -- countries which together hold sway over 25% of the world's land, 40% of its population and a combined GDP of $15.435 trillion dollars.&amp;nbsp; 
    The second event of our series, which took place on June 4, features panel discussions of investment issues in the BRIC countries as well as the role of transparency and the development of the rule of law within each country.&amp;nbsp; 
    Our&amp;nbsp;final September 1 session will assess the challenges of managing intellectual property rights in the BRICs and explore&amp;nbsp;how best to calibrate&amp;nbsp;U.S. policy toward these countries in&amp;nbsp;the years ahead.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Please join us to engage with leading experts as we conclude our series discussion of&amp;nbsp;the current and future significance of the BRIC economies and what their influence means&amp;nbsp;for our nation's economic interests.&amp;nbsp; 
